article.headline: Louisiana Tech 73, Idaho 72
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Trey McDowell scored 25 points as Louisiana Tech held on for a 73-72 victory over Idaho on Saturday night. Jerome Richardson added a season-high 15 points and Chad McKenzie had 12 points for the Bulldogs (6-12, 4-2 Western Athletic Conference). Keoni Watson led Idaho (3-15, 1-5) with 21 points, but missed a last-second shot that would have given the Vandals their second straight win. Darin Nagle scored 20 points for Idaho, including a 3-pointer from approximately 28 feet for the game's final basket with 15.8 seconds left. Nagle drew a charging foul from McKenzie at midcourt to give Idaho the ball with 12.4 seconds left, but Watson's short, running jumper failed to fall at the end. Louisiana Tech led by small margins most of the game, including 30-27 at the half. Nagle scored 11 points in the final 7:36 after Louisiana Tech had expanded its lead to 55-47. The Bulldogs outrebounded Idaho 40-21. The Bulldogs won for just the second time in 11 games away from home this season. McDowell, a senior guard who played two years of junior college basketball, had his second-highest scoring game in two years at Louisiana Tech -- one game after scoring a career-high 33 points Wednesday in an overtime win against New Mexico State. McDowell's season scoring average has risen from 10.5 to 12.6 in two games.
